tip.text: Found this place on Instagram. Good quality burgers at decent prices in a trendy location. Their special sauce is so good. Sweet potato fries were underwhelming.
Excellent coffee and baked goods. Love the white walls and marbles tiles. Friendly staff.

tip.text: Found this place by accident and it was one of the best coffee shops I visited in the city. The cakes are to die for, coffee is also good. Very spacious: good for working and also hanging out.
Hidden gem in the city. Steep prices for the city's standards but the quality is worth the price. Totally recommended. Its clientele is mostly girls talking selfies, though.
Seriously one of the best coffees in the city. Expect a line but it goes by quickly. No wifi.

tip.text: What a treat. If you're not staying at these luxurious villas, you can still enjoy the place while visiting this restaurant. Food and service were the best. Expensive. Many mosquitoes.
One of the best Mexican restaurants I've tried in all of Asia. Excellent and authentic tacos and quesadillas. The place is super lively and ideal for celebrations. An Instagram paradise.
This place is a must when visiting Ubud. It embodies the whole healthy, authentic and laid back concept that tourists expect when visiting this part of Bali. Seasonal dishes available.
The Revolver brand has the best coffee in Bali. Very small space with a few seats. Decent pastries and small meals. Friendly staff.
One of the best dim sum places in the city. Service, cleanliness, decor, food quality and size of portions are way above the average. Expensive but not comparatively excessive. A favorite!
